---------------------------------------------------------<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://fpc.state.gov/documents/organization/9041.pdf">fpc.state.gov/documents/o...n/9041.pdf</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
... top of page 7... i believe... it's not much and granted, it is dated almost 3 years ago... but then again has anything really changed since then?<br>
<br>
little frustrating... a lot of these CRS reports seem to refer to a document coded RL3119 - Terrorism: Near East Groups and State Sponsors... however, haven't been able to find that particular document.... ahha... found it...<br>
<br>
www.fas.org/irp/crs/RL31119.pdf<br>
<br>
page 35<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Frankly, I'm not too worried about my local radio free iraq station being bombed anytime soon. Yet this along with empty warheads are enough to start a war amidst a sea of global apprehension towards the US's quick approval of military force? <br>
<br>
We should be taking out Al Qaeda in its entirety. Theres no doubt about that...but where besides reading into G.W.'s ambiguous one-liners has there been any proof that Saddam = Al Qaeda?? People link Iraq and Sept. 11th as a means of generalizing that area of the world. Personally, I don't see any reason why a country who blatantly admits to violating the nuclear nonproliferation treaty like North Korea wouldn't be MORE likely to give an anti-american group weapons. Much moreso than Iraq.<br>
<br>
ps: thanks lasservien, who has no affiliation to my thoughts on the matter but supplied the information I'm using in my argument nonetheless.<br>
