My point is there has been SOME evidence and alot of speculation that we KNOW of linking Iraq and Bin Laden. I don't think it we now have or may ever have all the facts relating to the nature of that connection. Ask yourself one simple question ..... do you THINK the 2 are connected?<br>
<br>
 The point of any worthy debate or argument is to make points trying to convince the other side that your view is worthy. I am willing to accept the fact that POSSIBLY war at this stage is not needed (though I feel it is) if you will agree that there is a possibility (and I think a strong one) that the 2 are linked. What angers me in this whole debate is the fact that people are saying war is not the answer, in fact Palater said he doesn't support war .. EVER... WHAT IS THEN? Its easy to say &quot;You're doing this wrong&quot;, but not so easy to sugguest an alternate idea. It is exactly this type of pacifism which makes us vulnerable. Once that line has been crossed (and it has been) where people are not affraid to come into our back yards and attack us, we must do whatever it takes to defend ourselves from them.  We don't know all the facts and all the intelligence our government has, we may never know. But we must trust those in power to lead us and to make the difficult decissions that none of us would ever want to make.<br>
